{"TopicId":212908,"ForumId":196,"TopicTitle":"Landing Legs Detach","CreatedByName":"Astronut8997","CreatedById":226431,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T03:15:48Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Astronut8997","CreatedById":226431,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-02-26T03:15:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLanding Legs fall off when reloading a quick save. The legs stay stationary to where the reload occurred if on orbit but will fall to the ground if on a celestial body.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NaughtyMonster","CreatedById":210559,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-19T21:00:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve had the same issue recur several times. Mostly, as Astronut says, when reloading a quick save. Here are a few examples from Low Mun Orbit - where I\u0027ve had the most trouble:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Mun%20Kraken%20legs.jpg?raw=1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/kbt4fkah6qnaqfz/Mun%20Kraken%20legs.jpg?raw=1\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Mun%20Kraken%20legs%202.jpg?raw=1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/fjwcrsft9bw06aw/Mun%20Kraken%20legs%202.jpg?raw=1\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Mun%20Kraken%20legs%201.jpg?raw=1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/eetht2ndwwsxwqh/Mun%20Kraken%20legs%201.jpg?raw=1\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut just now (19/03/23) it happened in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E when I staged:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022LKO%20staging%20Kraken%20legs.jpg?raw=1\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.dropbox.com/s/ragoajg9vpqjhsl/LKO%20staging%20Kraken%20legs.jpg?raw=1\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve only ever had this problem with the large legs (so far...).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst three images v0.1.0.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFourth image v0.1.1.0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWindows 10 \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E i7-7700 \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E MSI GTX 1650 (GDDR6) \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E 32GB RAM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-03-19T21:11:13Z\u0022 title=\u002203/19/2023 09:11  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 19, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by NaughtyMonster\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vortygont","CreatedById":223549,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-03-23T20:07:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI saw this problem in several KSP2 videos, here is exampe(of course not my video)\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://youtu.be/AUuAtriK8_o?t=850\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://youtu.be/AUuAtriK8_o?t=850\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0. Legs were detached after they were extended\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also had this bug several times, but in ver 0.1.0.0. It is crtitical bug which brokes game in the most important moments. I hope it will be fixed in the nearest update\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}